<subSubSection id="4D1A7651F37048B20FC83C466F2C7E84" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="notes">
<paragraph id="2742D64255CC2455CADD52BCD566E39D" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D281F2AB83D877ECA925EC5E8DCB465D" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
This species was previously recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="DFBF1008B781AF545F2FC4BD5097D241" author="Valletta, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Monthly Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="45 - 46" refId="B19" refString="Valletta, A, 1971. A preliminary list of the Hymenoptera Aculeata (excluding ants) of the Maltese Islands. Entomologist's Monthly Magazine 107: 45 - 46" title="A preliminary list of the Hymenoptera Aculeata (excluding ants) of the Maltese Islands." volume="107" year="1971">Valletta (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B7A6ABD3BB0E706F82D9B7FA9F9368E" author="Erlandsson, S" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="11 - 93" refId="B6" refString="Erlandsson, S, 1972. Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries. Eos Madrid 48: 11 - 93" title="Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries." volume="48" year="1972">Erlandsson (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="28B99FD476D2EDC7D8E51C201BEB28BD" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. The Maltese Islands are inhabited by the nominate subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="66B2A2A9389902038C8CDFF91FB6D3F1" authority="oculatum" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Rhynchium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhynchium oculatum subsp. oculatum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oculatum" subSpecies="oculatum">
<emphasis id="4CCAA93CD81660038DCE515ED503E679" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Rhynchium oculatum oculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1781), a taxon occurring in southern Europe and North Africa. Another subspecies occurs in Europe - 
<taxonomicName id="3C85FDE4B91AF0FB4B8E02D601079CB5" authorityName="Giordani Soika" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Rhynchium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Rhynchium oculatum subsp. hebraeum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="oculatum" subSpecies="hebraeum">
<emphasis id="F302443F675477CD79C798449D4C157D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Rhynchium oculatum hebraeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Giordani Soika, 1952, which inhabits the Balkans and the Middle East (
<bibRefCitation id="4BF2A5E488FC5CA5FD2A1E487E15DFEA" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B12" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1998b. Vespoidea und Sapygidae gesammelt auf der Insel Samos (Hymenoptera: Eumenidae, Masaridae, Sapygidae). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30/1: 155-161." title="Vespoidea und Sapygidae gesammelt auf der Insel Samos (Hymenoptera: Eumenidae, Masaridae, Sapygidae). Linzer Biologische Beitraege 30 / 1: 155 - 161." year="1998 b">Gusenleitner 1998b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="A8A46C0106977009ACA60B424EA723C0" author="Castro, L" journalOrPublisher="Boletin Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="259 - 278" refId="B4" refString="Castro, L, Sanza, F, 2009. Aportacion al conocimiento de los Vespidae (Hymenoptera) de Sierra Nevada (Espana), con alguno comentarios taxonomicos. Boletin Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa 45: 259 - 278" title="Aportacion al conocimiento de los Vespidae (Hymenoptera) de Sierra Nevada (Espana), con alguno comentarios taxonomicos." volume="45" year="2009">Castro and Sanza 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E19EEC5E2567BC6DB2E4F671FE3C59B6" genus="R." lsidName="R. oculatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" rank="species" species="oculatum">
<emphasis id="486E4B71008DCA9A19B57B78A343E58F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">R. oculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the largest eumenine in the Maltese Islands, is very common locally and often nests within pre-existing cavities such as hollow reeds and crevices in wood. Its parasitoid 
<taxonomicName id="39C53CD91FB209704354135CE9DC2C37" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" genus="Macrosiagon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrosiagon ferruginea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis id="3DB804BF627120DC36F20575EB224122" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Macrosiagon ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="7E345AC692EF5BBF304D51ED76D80E64" class="Insecta" genus="Macrosiagon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="24470A5DFE1C2302814338F6802B0116" class="Insecta" family="Ripiphoridae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ripiphoridae</taxonomicName>
) is also present in the Maltese Islands.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
